laboratory_examinations.findings: Appendix is dilated measuring up to 1 cm in diameter with mild hyperemia of the wall and surrounding inflammatory fat stranding. No free air or evidence of abscess formation is seen. No free fluid is noted. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and adrenal glands appear unremarkable. Loops of small and large bowel are of normal size and caliber. No pathologically enlarged lymph nodes are seen.
